				\begin{document}$$\sigma$$\end{document}σ) significantly increases (filled bar). The result shows that a devastating marine heatwave in the eastern North Pacific, surpassing the severity anticipated solely from the global warming trend, is inherently coupled to a seemingly opposing freezing winter in North America, featured by an unusually frequent occurrence of cold spells.

